name: Hemoglobin diamond
description:
A red blood cell contains over 250 million hemoglobin complexes. Hemoglobin is an iron-containing metalloprotein composed of four protein chains containing a ring-like heme group. Hemoglobin transports oxygen from the lungs to the rest of the body by reversibly binding oxygen to the iron in each heme.
